            {
                "s2_paper_id": "b07b1caea54b5c28747b50cb10949e1055889075",
                "title": "Beltrami system and 1-quasiconformal embeddings in higher dimensions",
                "year": 2017,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 0,
                "reference_count": 16,
                "abstract": "In this paper we derive necessary and sufficient conditions for a smooth surface in Rn+1 to admit a local 1-quasiconformal parameterization by a domain in Rn (n >= 3). We then apply these conditions to specific hypersurfaces such as cylinders, paraboloids, and ellipsoids. As a consequence, we show that the classical Liouville theorem about the rigidity of 1-quasiconformal maps between domains in Rn with n >= 3 does not extend to embeddings of domains into a higher dimensional space.",
